tafsir[12]{c,v,t}:
  54,28,"Tell them that the water of their well is divided between them and the she-camel: one day for it and one day for them. Each turn will be attended by its owner alone on the day allocated to him."
  54,30,"So reflect- O people of Makkah - how was my punishment to them? And how was my warning to others about their punishment?"
  54,31,"I sent on them a single blast which destroyed them and they became like dry trees that are used by a person who makes a fence for his sheep."
  54,35,"I rescued them from the punishment as My favour upon them. I give a recompense similar to the one I gave to Lot to those who are thankful to Allah for His favours."
  54,36,"Lot warned them of My punishment but they disputed with one another about his warning and they rejected it."
  54,37,"Lot’s people tried to tempt him to give them access to the angels who were his guests with the intention of doing an indecent act. I obliterated their eyes so they did not see them and I said to them: Taste my punishment and the result of My warning to you."
  54,39,"It will be said to them: Taste My punishment that I sent down on you and the result of Lot’s warning to you."
  54,41,"My warning came to the people of Pharaoh on the tongue of Moses and Aaron (peace be upon them)."
  54,44,"Or do these disbelievers from the people of Makkah say: We are all together and well-defended against those who have evil designs against us and who wish to break up our unity?"
  54,45,"The group of these disbelievers will be defeated and they will turn their backs before the believers. This occurred on the day of Badr."
  54,47,"Those who are guilty of disbelief and sins are astray from the truth and in punishment and difficulty."
  54,48,"On the day when they will be dragged in the Fire on their faces and it will be said to them in rebuke: Taste the punishment of the Fire."